<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2352] zero-length strings should result in zero-length ByteBuffers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2352</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;o.a.c.db.marshal.AbstractType.fromString()&lt;/tt&gt; methods should return an empty &lt;tt&gt;ByteBuffer&lt;/tt&gt; when passed a zero-length string, (empty bytes do &lt;tt&gt;validate()&lt;/tt&gt; properly).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12501733">CASSANDRA-2352</key>
            <summary>zero-length strings should result in zero-length ByteBuffers</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
