                                        <fixVersion>0.8 beta 1</fixVersion>
                                    <component>Legacy/CQL</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13008143" author="gdusbabek" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2011 21:23:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008158" author="urandom" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2011 21:38:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008176" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2011 21:55:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;we actually keep BBUtil.EMPTY_BYTE_BUFFER to avoid allocating lots of zero-length BBs, can you update post-commit?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008289" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2011 02:38:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;went ahead and did this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008318" author="urandom" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2011 04:13:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Jonathan!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008359" author="stuhood" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2011 07:20:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this mean empty strings will validate as column names?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008423" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2011 13:16:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have separate checks in ThriftValidation for name.remaining() != 0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing this is to make it easier to do slicing, where empty start is valid?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13008467" author="urandom" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2011 15:08:16 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Does this mean empty strings will validate as column names?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;AbstractType.validate()&lt;/tt&gt; methods already allow this.  As Jonathan says, wherever that&apos;s not acceptable, &lt;tt&gt;ThriftValidation&lt;/tt&gt; has tests to ensure name.remaining() != 0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13009949" author="hudson" created="Wed, 23 Mar 2011 01:28:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #797 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/797/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/797/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
